Disaster Relief Resource Management CRM
1.	Problem Statement
During disasters such as floods, earthquakes, or cyclones, relief organizations often face difficulties in tracking donations, allocating resources, and coordinating volunteers. The lack of real-time visibility leads to inefficiencies and delays in reaching affected communities.
2.	Project Overview
The proposed Salesforce CRM solution will manage relief resource donations, track inventory, assign volunteers, and monitor beneficiary distribution. It will provide real-time dashboards for NGOs, government agencies, and donors to ensure transparency and accountability during disaster response.
3.	Objectives
-	Improve Resource Management: Track donations and inventory effectively.
-	Automate Allocation: Assign resources and volunteers based on priority needs.
-	Provide Real-Time Reporting: Show live dashboards of aid distribution.
-	Ensure Transparency: Keep donors, NGOs, and government updated.
-	Enhance Relief Efficiency: Reduce delays and ensure resources reach the right beneficiaries.
